        <h1>Darjeeling Itinerary - 3 Days, 2 Nights</h1>







        <h2>Day 1: Arrival and Sightseeing</h2>



        <p>Upon arrival in Darjeeling, check-in at your hotel and take some time to rest. In the afternoon, visit the following attractions:</p>



        <ul>



            <li><strong>Himalayan Mountaineering Institute</strong> - Learn about the history of mountaineering in the Himalayas.</li>



            <li><strong>Padmaja Naidu Himalayan Zoological Park</strong> - Home to several endangered species including the red panda and snow leopard.</li>



            <li><strong>Tea Garden</strong> - Enjoy a walk through a tea garden and learn about tea production.</li>



        </ul>



        <p>Return to your hotel for dinner and overnight stay.</p>







        <h2>Day 2: Local Sightseeing</h2>



        <p>After breakfast, embark on a full-day tour of Darjeeling's key attractions:</p>



        <ul>



            <li><strong>Tiger Hill</strong> - Start early to witness the stunning sunrise over Mount Kanchenjunga.</li>



            <li><strong>Ghoom Monastery</strong> - One of the oldest Tibetan Buddhist monasteries in Darjeeling.</li>



            <li><strong>Batasia Loop</strong> - A scenic railway loop with a war memorial.</li>



            <li><strong>Japanese Peace Pagoda</strong> - A beautiful structure promoting world peace with panoramic views of Darjeeling.</li>



        </ul>



        <p>Enjoy dinner at a local restaurant and return to your hotel for overnight stay.</p>







        <h2>Day 3: Departure</h2>



        <p>After breakfast, check-out from the hotel. Depending on your departure schedule, you can visit the following places:</p>



        <ul>



            <li><strong>Darjeeling Mall</strong> - A popular place for shopping and relaxing.</li>



            <li><strong>St. Andrew's Church</strong> - A historical church with beautiful architecture.</li>



        </ul>



        <p>Proceed to the airport or railway station for your onward journey.</p>







